Change-Id: Iff1f9a8c1ae7d565558fa12bbfe27fe642f6ad2f","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/commits/38f4134e6884fb1d766999486a72810ebae6acf5"},{"sha":"9e3c906aca96739cc263fa1bc9671252fe084c9d","author":{"name":"Prakalp Srivastava","email":"7da1985d121fd79537822bb42be62798d2d2aa23@google.com"},"message":"Pass to mark input-output pairs of cluster_func that read/write to same resource as aliases.

Earlier this was done for device variables only as part of tf-tpu-merge-variables-with-execute pass. Aliasing information (which enables HLO input/output buffer memory optimizations) need not be restricted to same constraints as tf-tpu-merge-variables-with-execute pass.

This change decouples this optimization from tf-tpu-merge-variables-with-execute and adds it as a new pass - tf-tpu-mark-input-output-aliases with relaxed constraints. This enables populating HloInputOutputAliasConfig in HloModuleProto even for those input-outputs corresponding to variables that cannot be merged with TPUExecute (for example, host resource variables) leading to input/output buffer optimization on device.

PiperOrigin-RevId: 366623286
Change-Id: I502f381c58b7414bf402a9c5d2a3a4989cb36155","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/commits/9e3c906aca96739cc263fa1bc9671252fe084c9d"},{"sha":"13a747ba671c0e8e4d03c7fec33831fc72e44491","author":{"name":"Prakalp Srivastava","email":"7da1985d121fd79537822bb42be62798d2d2aa23@google.com"},"message":"Enable tf-device-mark-input-output-aliases pass in bridge phase 1 pipeline.

This captures input output pairs of device computation that read/write to the same resource variable. Passing that information to XLA compiler enables device memory optimization.
